            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>Laoag City has an International Airport, a nearby Seaport in Currimao town, and numerous bus lines where people and goods are transited daily.</p>
            <p>From Manila, it is 45 minutes by plane and 80 minutes from Hongkong and Macau. By land, it is a 12-hour trip.</p>
            <p>Laoag is an hour drive north of the World Heritage City of Vigan.</p>
            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Whole month of February – In time for the City’s Pamulinawen Festival, a month-long festivity in commemoration of St. William the Hermit, the Patron Saint of Laoag City, which is celebrated on February 10.
                    It is during this time when Ilocano migrants from abroad, especially from Hawaii and California, come home and get recognized through coronation pageants and balls.</li>
            </ol>
